2019 KICKED MY ASS. I moved out of my childhood house and started renting my own. My anxiety and depression hit an all time high when I lost my rock, my grandpa to the cursed C. Word! Still miss him everyday. I lost a bunch of people who I thought were my friends but did things behind my back. I met a new best friend who I've been through hell and back with and I'm forever grateful for. On the plus though I got multiple new tattoos,  got signed to a few small  modeling companies, and got to attend the Ski Mask concert ft. (R.I.P. Juicewrld). I gained two amazing in laws and even gained an adorable nephew! 2019 was nothing short of a rollercoaster with a mostly downward slope but I can't wait to see what 2020 has in store.
Happy New Years Everybody!üéÜüçæü•Ç
